/target
daemon.err
daemon.out
probe.txt
.claude/

# Locally built binaries for testing before a release. The published ones
# come from release.yml, which also emits the SHA256SUMS `upgrade` verifies;
# these are unsigned throwaways and must never be committed or shipped.
/dist/

# CycloneDX SBOMs are generated from Cargo.lock on demand and attached to
# releases by release.yml; a committed copy would just go stale.
*.cdx.json

# The third-party attribution notice is generated from Cargo.lock by
# `cargo about generate` and packaged into every release archive, where the
# licences actually require it to be. A committed copy would go stale on each
# dependency bump without anything noticing.
THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md

# Droppings from desktop environments and file managers. This project is
# developed from macOS, Windows and Linux machines at once, and every one of
# these is written by the OS on its own — often just by looking at a folder —
# so they arrive without anyone deciding to add them. They say nothing about
# the project and are listed for all three platforms on every platform, since
# whoever's machine creates one is not the one who notices it.

# macOS. `.DS_Store` holds Finder's per-folder view settings; `._*` are
# AppleDouble sidecars that carry resource forks onto non-HFS filesystems,
# and `Icon\r` really does end in a carriage return.
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*
Icon?
.DocumentRevisions-V100
.fseventsd
.Spotlight-V100
.TemporaryItems
.Trashes
.VolumeIcon.icns
.com.apple.timemachine.donotpresent

# Windows. Thumbs.db and its variants are Explorer's thumbnail caches;
# desktop.ini holds per-folder appearance; *.stackdump is a Cygwin crash dump.
Thumbs.db
Thumbs.db:encryptable
ehthumbs.db
ehthumbs_vista.db
[Dd]esktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/
*.stackdump
*.lnk

# Linux. `.directory` is Dolphin's per-folder settings, `.Trash-*` the
# per-user trash on a shared mount, and `.nfs*`/`.fuse_hidden*` appear when a
# still-open file is deleted on those filesystems.
.directory
.Trash-*
.nfs*
.fuse_hidden*

# Editor leftovers of the same accidental kind: swap files and backups written
# beside the file being edited. Editor *configuration* directories are left
# out on purpose — those are a choice a project makes, not something an OS
# does behind your back.
*~
*.swp
*.swo
